        published: true,
        jobType: "full-time",
        description: "The Medical City Iloilo is seeking a qualified Radiologic Nurse who will play a pivotal role in delivering safe, efficient, and compassionate nursing care to patients undergoing diagnostic imaging and interventional radiology procedures. This position ensures that every patient receives high-quality care and support throughout their radiologic journey \u2014 in alignment with the institution\u2019s commitment to excellence, innovation, and patient-centered service.\n\nThis role reports directly to the Chief Radiologic Technologist\n\nWhat\u2019s the Role All About?\n\nJob responsibilities include, but are not limited to:\n- Assist radiologists and technologists during diagnostic and interventional radiology procedures.\n- Prepare, assess, and monitor patients before, during, and after radiologic examinations to ensure comfort and safety.\n- Administer medications, contrast agents, and sedation as prescribed, following strict safety and aseptic protocols.\n- Maintain accurate, detailed documentation of patient assessments, procedures, and outcomes.\n- Provide assistance in handling and positioning patients during imaging procedures.\n- Respond promptly to medical emergencies within the department and perform life-saving interventions when necessary.\n- Educate patients and their families on pre- and post-procedure care, instructions, and follow-up requirements.\n- Uphold infection control, radiation safety, and patient confidentiality standards.\n- Participate in the maintenance of equipment and ensure proper inventory of supplies used in radiologic procedures.\n- Collaborate with physicians, radiologic technologists, and other healthcare professionals to ensure seamless, high-quality patient care.\n\nWho Are We Looking For?\n\nAn effective Radiologic Nurse must demonstrate the following qualities and competencies:\n\nValues-Driven Behaviors: Embodies The Medical City Iloilo\u2019s institutional values of integrity, compassion, collaboration, and excellence in all aspects of care.\n\nClinical Expertise: Possesses the technical knowledge and practical skills necessary to provide nursing care in radiology and interventional procedures.\n\nCritical Thinking and Adaptability: Responds effectively to complex clinical situations and emergencies with sound judgment and precision.\n\nProfessionalism and Empathy: Provides holistic, patient-centered care that prioritizes safety, dignity, and comfort.\n\nCollaboration and Communication: Works effectively within a multidisciplinary team and communicates clearly with both colleagues and patients.\n\nQualifications:\n- Must be a Registered Nurse recognized by the Professional Regulation Commission (PRC).\n- Preferably with at least one (1) year of clinical experience in Radiology, Critical Care, or Emergency Nursing.\n- Training and certification in Basic Life Support (BLS) and Advanced Cardiac Life Support (ACLS) are highly preferred.\n- Strong knowledge of radiologic procedures, patient monitoring, and emergency response protocols.\n- Proficient in documentation, patient assessment, and the use of electronic health record systems.\n- Willing to work in a hospital-based, fast-paced, and team-oriented environment.",
